flowRoot.flowPara: Here we have, depending on inputs from
CU, all combinations of A>B, A>=B and so on (IMPORTANT: ALSO A>0 ETC.). This goes both to output (to set some register as flag if so is needed) and to the select control of a multiplexer.

That multiplexer selects wether to increase PC normally or to add B to PC, thus implementing conditional branches: non-conditional jumps are then equivalent to "branch if 0=0" (A=0 coming from R0, check equality with 0 in comparator, use it to drive multiplexer).
Control signals for shifting logic: "shift" high to shift, otherwise rotate; "left" high to operate left, otherwise operate right, "logic" high to do a logical shift, otherwise arithmetic.
It supports AND, OR, XOR and variations of shift.
"110"=>AND, OR, XOR, SHL, SHR, SAL, SAR, ROR, ROL;
